76561198176092179,Recommended,313340,26511535,"Posted: 9 November, 2016",all,MercenarySeive,"Now, there's not really much to this, but I'd still recommend it. First thing: gameplay is almost non-existant, so I'll refrain from calling this a game.The visuals of this program are pretty impressive, even if they are simple at times. On the lowest settings (which I usually use since my computer isn't really a ""gaming"" computer), it almost looks like a watercolour painting that you can interact with.As I said before, gameplay is lacking. What isn't, in my opinion, is sound. Users can make music with the keyboard, and can play around with it to make or recreate little songs. Some specific songs give interesting effects or filters to the world, like raining blood or frogs, or even ""snowglobe mode.""I'd say it's a neat little program and deserves a place in anyone's library, especially if they enjoy just sitting around and watching things change around them. A lot like Viridi, but without the daily upkeep that it needed."
