,Recommended,313340,13947601,"Posted: 11 January, 2015",all,[slckr]robilar5500,"This is an interesting experiment. it really isnt a game per se, but it is well worth the dollar you will spend on it. It is as the title says....a Mountain, which is a god, a single great entity, and being that is finding a sense for itself and asking the basic questions beings ask themselves...why am I, who am I, am I alone, and so on. While this is happening, weather changes, day and night cycles, and random objects crash into its surface. You can use the keyboard to craft/play songs, many of which unlock various weather and artifact features, thoughts, and so on. I recommend leaving this game open and checking on it every so often to see what it is doing and has done while you were away.When you grow weary of it, you can destroy your mountain, wipe its surface clean, or whatever.This is something people should be experiencing. A simple and yet deep experience.10/10"
