,Not Recommended,313340,13337324,"Posted: 12 December, 2014",all,intox. Requiesta de Silencia,"Mountain is a neat little time-sink where you watch a chunk of rock slowly turn and grow while constantly making telltale games-style choices, like at what point the best time would be to blow it up.In all seriousness, I don't get this game. I can appreciate a good art game like Dear Esther and Gone Home but at least there you had some level of agency. In this game you have gimmicks instead, such as raining frogs and raining hearts. I generated a new mountain several times and failed to see much of a difference between them.It feels more like an artistic statement than an artistic game, and while I don't mind artistic statements I'm not sure I like being charged so that somebody else can make one. If I just wanted to stare at something moving and growing I have a really nice hourglass that I got as a gift (I mean REALLY nice!) and I feel like I'd get just as much enjoyment watching that. In fact I just confirmed it. It moves at more than 20 frames per second, has better sound effects, and if a celestial body comes crashing down it won't look like someone attached a translucent red glass texture to a very low polygon sphere.So I can't recommend this artistic statement. It has some charm but that alone isn't enough. If you want to see my first impressions of this game, check out my video below. I do indie game first impressions every so often.https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=i2jcSsICMTY"
