,Recommended,313340,13803549,"Posted: 3 January, 2015",all,a sprayerxx,"Upon buying the game ""Mountain"", it was delivered to my library immediately which suprised me positively.As for the package for this product, I can say I am satisfied. The game was not damaged after delivery, only a tiny little scratch on the backside, but I personally do not find it disturbing as it does NOT affect gameplay in any way.The packafe contains the game, forums and guides. Then I launched the game, not before having read through the license of agreement and notes for the safe use of this game carefully.The intro shows all companies involved in the making of this game. Luckily, the intro can be skipped upon pressing enter, this will save a lot of time in the future.The graphics are very good looking- thanks to the physic/graphic engine develoved just for this game. I myself disliked the strong effects at times, referring to the motion blur and lens flare, luckily it is possible to turn these effects off in the video option screen. The graphics can be ranked as ""Next-gen"" for sure.I've benchmarked this game on two different machines; one AMD and one intel/nVidia run each. It is a slight better performance on the AMD machines, but that might be just me.Unfortunately, the game did NOT support my Logitech G27 Steering wheel, so I had to stick to my Razer Deathadder 2015 Chroma and Savior gaming keyboard. This is a real bummer, looking at the fact I bought this Logitech G27 steering wheel just for the sake of enjoying ""Mountain"" even more.I will not talk much about the gameplay itself since I do not want to spoil anything, however I will talk about the mechanism the game works with.The playground is a open world, taking place on a mountain, based on surviving the difficulities of mother nature.It features a lot of variants on how the game can be completed. Please keep in mind that there is no real way of failing, however there is no way to achieve 100% either. Due to the missing challenge at occasions I found the game not too interesting at times, however I have enjoyed the gameplay so far.I myself think trying and finding out for yourself is the best way of knowing whether you like the game or not :)TL;DR: The game is a very challenging game, newbies will find themself helpless at times, but luckily there are many guides to read through to help out.Package and delivery: 9/10Graphics: 8/10Gameplay: 8/10Hardware compatibility: 7/10Overall: 8/10.I hope I could help you people out!"
