,Not Recommended,313340,13251337,"Posted: 6 December, 2014",all,microfloppy,"NOTE: For review with screenshots, please visithttp://microfloppy.net/2014/12/06/mountain/Mountain was nominated in the 2014 Game Awards in the category ""Games for Change"".  Don't let yourself be fooled however: It is not a game that can be played. Mountain is a zero player game; an animated wallpaper.You are born a Mountain, floating through space. You experience the turning of time and seasons. Things crash into you on occation. And you ponder on your existence. You can, to a very limited extent, affect what happens on-screen, but this doesn't extend beyond different animations.The ambient music (mostly wind or rain) is atmospheric, the imagery is pretty, and you can play tunes using your keyboard.I can't say I regret buying it because I had some fun with it and it was only 66c, but it's not something I would recommend anyone buying.2/10 fireflies"
