,Recommended,313340,11879340,"Posted: 26 August, 2014",all,76561193705059552,"It is what it is, don't get mad that you didn't do any research before you spent a dollar on something that you had no idea what it was going to be. Personnally I really liked this. It is basically a screen saver, except it feels alive.I started to feel attached to the mountain I had made, I even found out a way to remove junk from my mountain by throwing it off, or by playing a melody. I was devastated when I played the melody from Close Encounters. My mountain was destroyed by the eye of blindness, it was sad. I ocasionally I leave this running in the background just to see if anything will happen. Its not a game, but its not really anything else other than a game. Just like making Bonsai trees isn't really like being a full-on gardener, but it basically is.Worth the $1? I don't know, you decide. It's not hard to figure out if you will hate this or appreciate this. I was glad I got it. If it's a game, then it is a really ammusing cheap take on what games are and how we play them (like Little Inferno). If it's a screen saver, then it is a really good interactive screen saver that has way more depth, beauty, and humor than any screensaver I have ever used.I will give it a thumbs up but you don't have to, and thats okay, just don't buy ignorantly and then complain. It is what it is and you are not forced to buy it. Just ask the mountain what he thinks of himself, he will tell you, and in a very contemplative way too."
