,Not Recommended,313340,11874332,"Posted: 26 August, 2014",all,FlatDevice,"Um well, this is a different take on the concept of ""game"".  You have a mountain which rotates and accumulates random objects (the first object to crash into my mountain was an umbrella -- wtf, how did an umbrella get into space is what I want to know).  On occasion, the mountain thinks very mountain-y thoughts, like ""I'm diggin' on this storm!"" or ""Hey wow this spooky night is the bomb!"" (paraphrased).  The player can pick up the random objects and set them down again (exciting).  Other than that, I'm not sure if this ""game"" does anything else -- well, there are the musical notes one can play which sound pretty nice when scrolled way out, so that's a thing.All in all -- I shouldn't like this ""game"", but I sorta do, but honestly as it is I can't recommend it. Sure, it's kind of zen to just look into it from time to time and see what other crap your mound of spacedirt has picked up, but there's just not anything else to it.  I hope some civilizations evolve or something like that to break up the monotony, but maybe that's too much to hope for.  Maybe worth getting only when it's far less than 99 cents; I kind of feel like I overpaid."
