,Recommended,313340,33241959,Posted: 4 July,all,The Real XXXTentacion,"It Could Be Better but It's Worth the Cheap PricePeople who say ""This is not an actual game"" don't know how to play this game. This game is a decent experience, especially for the price. Its an idle game for the most part but there are several things that players can do to interact with the game. You leave this game alone running in the background while you do something else. I usually play this game while I'm downloading a bigger one.In the game you can press certain keys on your keyboard to play musical keys and if you play them in a certain sequence you can cause events to happen. One of these events includes summoning an apocalypse onto the mountain. You can then frantically spam your keyboard to play musical notes inorder to defend yourself from said apocalypse. Repeat several times over for some of the achievements.If you can't read whats above because you're a lazykcufjust read this pro and cons list:Pros:1. Over 24 hours of gameplay if you want all the achievements.2. A total of 31 aesthetic achievements available.3. It's less than one dollar.Cons:1. Zero to no action unless you summon a apocalypse.2. Under a few minutes of active gameplay if you don't go for the achievements."
