,Not Recommended,313340,14787696,"Posted: 7 March, 2015",all,Alekai,"If this game cost more I would have an even longer review; it is not a game. If you want to say that ""It's supposed to delve into philosophy and expand the definition of a game"" thing, fine. good for you. but don't put it on steam. This is literally nothing more than a rotating entity with changing backgrounds. I don't want to be to hard on it (Because it's only a dollar), but it has no purpose other than to waste your time. I could hop onto Netbeans and code something like this in under an hour, and this really worries me about the gaming market. With all the press that this game is getting, and amount of copies sold of this tiny game, some people will start making games like this simply to make a quick buck and write them off as games that ""delve into philosophy and expand the definition of a game"" to cover their greed. I don't understand why so many people give this a positive review, as it doesn't deserve it and only encourages people to make clones of it."
