76561198037281221,Recommended,313340,13957899,"Posted: 12 January, 2015",all,Marvin,"Mountain is a metaphor for life: barren, purposeless, spinning around in circles. That's how Mountain looked like at first but look closer and you will see all the trees, rocks and flowers growing around it. And isn't life just like that? We often neglect things that we already have.We sometimes feel stuck, with nothing good happening in our life. Every day is the same as the day before it. That's how Mountain is like as well if you just keep staring at it. But go back to it an hour or so later and you may be surprised to find a giant dice has landed on it. Doesn't life surprise us much in the same way as well?And the mountain's incline? It represents the challenges that we have to overcome to reach the peak of our potential. Often it may seem unreachable, just like how the peak of Mountain is usually covered in clouds. But at the perfect moment, the clouds pass by and you can see the beautiful future ahead of you.If you zoom out far enough, you can see Mountain covered in bright light, and the entire universe surrounding it. This implies how small we are at life and that there is an entire universe out there to explore and experience. Mountain is imploring us to go out there and make the most out of the short time given to us.As I close this game and go to sleep tonight, I know deep in my heart that I have grown to be a better man. Thank you Mountain for making me realize life's true meaning."
