rent Interpatations But Mine Is That This ""Game"" Is A Metaphor For Life. It Acts Like A Wake Up Call And With It's Simple But Beautiful Art Direction, It Kinda Prompts You To Leave Your Computer And Explore The Outside World And This Is Why It Appeals To Me.In Conclusion, This Is A ""Game"" That Provokes Discussion. I Usually Buy Games For My Steam Friends For Christmas And This Year, I'm Going To Send Them This Because It Would Be Nice To See How Other People See It. Games Allow Us To Escape Reality With Examples Like GTA's Gangsta Lifestyle Or With No Man Sky's Space Exploration And This ""Game"" Is Something That Pulls From That Reality And Makes Us Think About The Real Life We Have Been Given Before Us, Make Us Go Back In Time To A Time When People Only Had Nature To Entertain Them Nad When You Think About It, Nature Is One Of The Reasons Why Evolution And Our Pursuit For Techlogy Lead Us To Where We Are Today. In A Simple Statment, It's Just A Nice Little Tool That Reminds Us There's More To Life. Now Excuse Me While I Go And Play Painkiller."
