76561198057767761,Recommended,313340,22111135,"Posted: 28 March, 2016",all,Spuds MacKenzie,"This is a tough one to reccommend or to not reccommend. As all things are, this game is completely relative to your opinion. (Believe me, this game will arouse a strong opinion.) I consider it more of an art project than a video game. There's no purpose or controls, just the Mountain.You draw images based on the queue of the Mountain. Based on these images, your Mountain is decorated in odd objects. Strange philosophical sayings cross the screen periodically, and these are to represent the thoughts and feelings of your Mountain. Confused yet?I typically let it run while I am asleep. I get the suurprise, and sometimes horror, of what has crashed into my Mountain during the night. Once again, don't expect a traditional ""video game"", but more a ""video game-esque"" art project."
