,Recommended,313340,11786266,"Posted: 19 August, 2014",all,pliable,"First off, if you see any review that has a playtime of less than an hour, ignore it because it's more than likely a child crying in impotent rage about how ""dis game dum"" simply because their feeble brain can't handle a concept like this.With that being said, this isn't a game in the traditional sense. If you're expecting exxxtreme mountain action, well, you won't find any. I think calling it a game is rather inaccurate but, that's still okay.However, this is still a pretty neato piece of work. When you start the program, it presents words or questions to you and then has you draw something. The drawings are used as seeds to generate your mountain, to make each mountain unique.The idea is to just leave it running all the time, and you check on it whenever you want. I leave it minimized or off to the side, and then just completely disable the noise if I'm going to play another video game. The ambient noise the program makes is also very pleasant for general computer tasks. You can control the type of ambient noise by zooming in or out of your mountain, to get rainy/windy noises to a tao/zen like sound for outer space.As you check your mountain, you'll find more and more items piling up on it. As of this writing (and leaving it running for 12 hours), I've got a clock, a top-hat, a barbell, a biplane, and a cement brick. You can interact with these by clicking on the object and holding it down, and you can either toss it back out to space or redrop it somewhere else on the mountain.Various things will grow as well, and so far I've got various kinds of oakish and pine type trees going. You'll also get different kinds of weather going as well, depending on however the hell your mountain feels.There will be an audio cue at random, at which point a ""thought"" will pop up. The thoughts oddly put a smile on my face :). You can provoke ""thoughts"" as well by hitting '.' (the period key).So in summary, it's a really weird concept at first, but the key really is to just leave it running all the time. This piece is totally worth a dollar, maybe even more than that cause of how cool it is :)"
76561198034392042,Recommended,313340,11790085,"Posted: 19 August, 2014",all,Seth_Slax,"This game will leave you with a profound sense of zen.Although there is little you can do but observe for the first few minutes, it's still a fully immersive experience. When you're bored, play around with the musical notes and see if you can unlock the different modes. Turn down the graphical settings (to avoid overheating your GPU/CPU) and leave it to run while you're away. You'll be pleasantly surprised at how different your mountain is every time.Well worth the money. I would highly recommend this."
