,Recommended,313340,11771562,"Posted: 18 August, 2014",all,Mortal Motö,"Have you ever wondered how it feels like to stand still for millions of years? Me neither.This game is the most realistic simulator out there. All you do is stand still and wait for time to pass - just like a mountain! You can also, for some reason, play music with your keyboard. I can't imagine a better way to spend your time than playing happy version of Freezing Moon to your mountain. Unfortunately there's no grass in this game so I can't combine this realistic experience with my favorite hobby; watching the grass grow. Hopefully we'll get a grass DLC soon!This game also has a psychological test when you start to play. I in fact had to rely on a walkthrough to be able to pass this part of the game. I really like this feature - keeps adhd kids away from the game.The roleplay feel in this game is immersive! You can identify yourself as whatever mountain you want to be! Stone mountain? Sure! Grass mountain? Sure! Feminist-bipolar-misandric-racefluid-tumblr-mountain? Yup!I'd like to end this in-depth review by mentioning the insanely realistic weather system! Rain doesn't go through any roof! Mountain - 1, Skyrim - 0A rock solid 8/10 because it lacks grass."
