76561198088870092,Not Recommended,313340,13975847,"Posted: 13 January, 2015",all,ClickerOfCookies,"Even with a price-tag of only $1 I cannot recommend this game. Actually, I don't even think i could even call it a game at all. Calling it a game would suggest some sort of gameplay, some sort of meaningful interaction, something to do... all things this ""game"" almost entirely lacks. 99% of this ""game"" consists of just staring at a floating mountain as it slowly rotates. Yeah, that's it. It's about as interesting as it sounds. I've seen a lot of people praising this game as something innovative or something that challenges what a game is. Don't get me wrong, there are some games out there that are doing just that... this is not one of them.The game starts with you being given a vague subject and you draw out a little picture based on that. As far as I know it goes into seeding the RNG that creates the mountain. It doesn't really matter what you draw but it's probably the most interesting part of the game. After that you are shown your mountain. It just sits there slowly spinning as it changes from day to night and the seasons change. Every little bit some text will pop up and once in a great while some random object will land on you mountain. All you can do is wait, you can zoom in and out or rotate the mountain, you can play musical notes with the keyboard, and you can pick up the objects and drop them back down on the mountain. That's about all there is to it. Sounds like a lot of fun, eh?Mountain might be somewhat redeemed if it actually looked good. If the graphics were even decent it might make a good screen saver but sadly they are not. The graphics are poor and I have problems with textures flickering and such. It's just not that pretty to look at. The dev also recommends that it's something to leave running while you do other things but it's so poorly optimized that it uses much more resources that in should for what it is... So much more that some people have suggested that it could be a Bitcoin miner in disguise, lol. There's no reason to believe that but the fact is that it's a bit heavy for something that's meant to be running it the background.If you are looking for something to blow a dollar on there are definitely better things you could get."
