,Not Recommended,313340,31386857,Posted: 26 April,all,Verdantil,"Tags: Clicker - SlowAdditional Tags: Delete Local Content & Remove from libraryTLDR: Its trashMountain is a screensaver/contemplative clicker hybrid featuring some, assumed, procedural generation,  based on doodles the game asks you to draw early on. I have found little correlation between the drawing and the generation so I am assuming that is a gimmick to make you feel more connected to the creationOnce thats done the game will randomly grow little trees, have electric storms happen and other mini events. The game will also spout cryptic one liners here and there to keep you on your toes.If I had to find an equivalence somewhere it would be the tree of wisdom in Plants VS Zombies.Conclusion: Overall with the limited interaction both at creation, and afterwards that this software has with the player it would not really qualify as a game, so it is kind of a short lived curiosity piece that ends up cluttering the library"
