,Recommended,313340,13182070,"Posted: 1 December, 2014",all,JellyRaven,"This is not a game, it is a piece of art that has very limited interaction. If you enjoy looking at something beautiful and the emotional representation of this, then I would say $1 is a nice supporting price to pay for this kind of thing. After awhile random objects like anvils and soccer balls will show up that you can move around, but nothing else really happened, except changing weather. You can play your mountain tunes using the keyboard that act like basic piano notes, and the mountain will send a soft single note to let you know it's going to say something in writing on the top left of the screen. It can be interpreted as the changes in you or emotions that you can experience.This product is definitely not for everyone and some people will be confused by it or angry at the limited interactions, while others will find it beautiful and calming, enjoying the presence of the little mountain in the background of their computer.Pros:- Beautiful- Music and sound effects are calming, beautiful, and simple- Relaxing and emotional- Only $1- there are very subtle interactions that are really calmingCons:- Very limited interactions, it would be nice if you could sculpt your mountain or move the trees around- Most people will not like this game, as it is more art than a game.I am recommending this to you if you are an art person or somebody who enjoys relaxing sound effects and beautiful things, otherwise, I would recommend not buying this as you will most likely just be disappointed.If you like these types of things, I would suggest it be an 7.5/10, if you do not like these types of games, I would say a 1/10, it is hard to give a rating too."
