,Recommended,313340,11770416,"Posted: 18 August, 2014",all,Rye Bread,"Controls are simple and streamlined. I did appreciate a beautiful game such as this having different graphical settings as well. Occasionally,  indie games such as this do not give you options, just because of how simple it is *cough* The Plan *cough*. My computer is not exactly cutting edge so I was able to apprecieate this game almost as much as other people with the fancy new 800 series. This game has some really great features. I am able to watch my mountain as it progresses through life. Seeing every angle. I think this game is actuall superior to being a real mountain because you can actually see what is going on underneath a mountain. This is not something you could just do in everyday life. You also get neat features that give a nice roleplayin vibe during the mountain generating sequence. You are able to choose lineage among other things. I love hearing the thoughts of my mountain. It makes me start to question what mountains think about IRL. Do they feel joy, anger, depression, boredom or love? These emotions are there. In the form of weather. When it snows on this mountain, you FEEL his cold and, to an extent, lonliness. It makes me start to question what really is a mountain? Are they really just elevated land? Or something more? Something with a soul? This  game makes me question my previously negative stance on mountains. I shouldn't go into detail, but I was unfair to them. All it took was some understanding and observation to realize that mountains are people too.I give it an 8/10It would be 10/10 but it needs multiplayer of some sort. I hope the developers get this message because I want to play this game at a LAN party. Coop would be nice BUT I think competitive multiplayer would be sweet. Think of all the amazing competitions you could create. You would finally be able to see which person would make a better mountain."
