76561197971491551,Recommended,313340,17577457,"Posted: 16 August, 2015",all,jwrebholz,"Believe it or not, this actually isn't the stupidest game I've ever bought.  It's not even the stupidest game I've bought on Steam.  I've bought way stupider things than this.OK, so what is it? It's a ""game"" only in the loosest sense.  I bought it out of pure morbid curiosity. What I got was..a mountain floating in space.  You can move the camera around.  You can play music with your keyboard (and if you play certain songs, things can happen).  The point, near as I can tell, is...there isn't one.  It's a mountain, floating in the middle of space.  There's really not much to it.  That said, the ambient noises are oddly relaxing, and looking at it I almost can't help but feel ..tranquil.  It's rather bizarre.  I don't even really want to call this a game, since there's no real controls and no real objective.But ****, it was 99 cents.  I've spent worse dollars than this."
