,Recommended,313340,11952258,"Posted: 1 September, 2014",all,StuntMan9630,"If you look at most of the negative reviews on this game: ignore them.They don't know what they bought and don't understand how to use it.This is not a game. It is also not a screensaver. It slots in with many other games that let you play a bit, then you leave it for a bit. The best example I can give is the Virtual Villagers series. You play a bit, you leave it to let your villagers grow. Then you return, get an update, play a little more, go back to normal life.Modern games keep you fixated on the screen way too long. This breaks that rule and is much respected by me for doing so.Yes it's not perfect. But for £1? Can you expect perfection? If it could be made so that it's not as memory intensive, it would no longer have any negative aspects. The only negative aspect is the attitude of the people who buy it unknowingly.That was going to be the end, but whilst I was writing this review, I got a little update on my mountans thoughts and aquired a new object to add to the collection: a little black hatchback. This is how it should be played. And to all you haters who are here to moan at a lack of a game: I have no time for you."
