,Not Recommended,313340,12130997,"Posted: 17 September, 2014",all,Folstaria,"This game...Well, you can already see I've said I don't recommend it, but that's not because I didn't enjoy it.Mountain is a highly realistic mountain watching simulator, in which you can watch a mountain. I know, it sounds exciting already, but the best is still to come.You can play a piano. That's right, read that sentence again. You can play a piano. I put it here again so you can read it a third time. Your keyboard enables you to play a piano, and it's literally the most exciting thing I've ever done.I poured hours into this game (this does not show on my steam account because of reasons). Literally days, and this is where it all went wrong for me.I live in a house with my Mother, Father and Two dogs. Sadly, while playing this game and excitedly trying out all the different keys I could use to play the piano, I failed to hear my Mother shout as she fell down the stairs. She broke both of her legs and stayed there all day. When my Dad returned home, he tripped over her unconcious body and also broke his legs. At this point I was mastering Beethoven's Moonlight Sonata, having finished all of his other symphonies. I did not hear them shouting for help.The days came and went, the mail piled up on my doormat and the milk went bad outside the door. Eventually, after two months my neighbour came around to check on us, and roused me from my waking coma. I stepped downstairs and found that sadly my dogs had gone without food and taken to eating my parents. They had developed a taste for human flesh, and had already killed my neighbour, and had begun feasting on her.I left them to it, as I'd been out for a few minutes and missed playing Mountain, and continued playing for a few more weeks until my electricity was shut off. I then went downstairs, fought off my dogs with a toaster and made some soup and am now waiting to die. I am typing this with 19% battery left on my phone, as I could not find a laptop with enough charge to play more Mountain.Overall, I'd give this game a solid 11/10 for gameplay, however owing to it's addictive qualities which led to the early demise of both my parents, our concerned neighbour and my two beloved Dogs, I have had to lower this figure to a more conservative 8/10."
