,Recommended,313340,11864866,"Posted: 25 August, 2014",all,WolfEcho,"This is a long, but completely honest and unbiased review, if your considering buying mountain, read this first.First, the reviewers and reporters who made such a big fuss about this game, both good and bad, are turds. Take it for what it is, its a small time no-to-low budget game. Its not life changing, its not exactly special, its just unique because nobody else has thought of making a mountain the focus of a game before. Its not a new genre of game, its not going to cause a huge shift in the industry (damn I hope it won't, shooters will turn into an episode of the simpsons).Yes its pretty much a screensaver like everyone claims, because its not really an interactive game, you just sit and look at it (probably why reporters made such a huge fuss about it, had to be the high point of their day...). I do hope that improvements will be made to it, I'd consider mountain to be in beta state still because its lacking some basic features like being able to start a new game. It has potential to be better then it is, but that would mean adding a few levels of interactive features. How about subtle things like affecting the weather or events that change the shape of the mountain, the plantlife, the items on it, maybe even add some animals or stick men? The simulation idea is nice but its progressing way too slowly for me, consider adding a speed switch on how fast changes take place maybe?The people who complain about spending their one dollar, what else were you going to do with it anyway? buy a pack of chips or bottle of coke? Big freakin deal, you spent one dollar to pay for a game you can't create on your own without weeks of training, no matter how bad you think it is, at least have a little bit of respect for someone else's work.In conclusion, Mountain is a nice start to a game that you can leave on while your busy with other things around the house, its pleasant to look at on max quality settings even if its not the sharpest textures out there, but it needs improvement and additional input from the creator to make it a great small background game. It needs something to keep you interested for more then just a few hours."
