,Recommended,313340,11802101,"Posted: 20 August, 2014",all,Captain Burrito,"This is not a game for the weak of heart. I don't mean to say that it's too thrilling for the weak, but that if you have no love, imagination or patience, you will lose.This game inherits from the arguably thousands of years of contemplative puzzles that mankind has fixated on, none can be evidenced except by the person who experiences it and even then, only to themselves. There are no reactions and counterreactions, no immediate advancement and reward, no answers given. There is only quiet consideration, and your own mind. If these tools alone are not enough to lead you to the next step, then you will lose.It's a game simultaneously so easy it plays itself, and so difficult that most cannot even grasp it's basic underpinnings. A revolution for gaming that the rest of the artistic world has taken as de facto since the dawn of time.The only way to lose is not to play."
